# Python Code Style

## Core Rules

- Follow PEP 8 strictly.
- Keep maximum line length at 88 characters.
- Require type hints for all function parameters and return values.
- Require Google-style docstrings for all public methods.

## Maintainability Guidance

- Prefer explicit names over ambiguous abbreviations.
- Keep functions focused on a single responsibility.
- Use named constants or configuration values instead of hidden literals.
